The paper deals with algorithmic questions for concurrent systems, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of algebraic path properties and semiring operations suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The focus on program analysis and controlflow graphs suggests that it may belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The consideration of multiple queries and tradeoffs suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of graph algorithms and conditional optimality results suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
